Oh, I used to be smart and I used to be nice
 Now I’m neither of those

She feels like she’s changed for the worse, that this breakup had made her worse as a person. But she’s fine, really.

I’m doin’ fine
 Only losin’ my mind every once in a while
 And it’s been cool
 Only thinkin’ I’m doomed every time that I do
 Yeah, it’s a lot
 But it’s not as much as I used to
There’s a loose “good thing/bad thing” structure that show’s Annie’s pessimistic mindset and struggles with identity in the wake of her breakup

My times disappearin’
 I guess it’s been a year and

The entire song seems to be a meditation on the fallout of leaving a bad relationship.
This line could be reflecting upon how time seems to race past, leaving one feeling unproductive.

description.plain: Annie DiRusso really taps into that coming of age experience with this amazing song! It is the anthem for long nights, gas station food, 3am drives around the block, longing stares, and analyzing every little thing someone says to you. It embodies the feeling of not knowing what is going on between you and “that” person, and being almost fed up with wondering where you stand.

annotations:
I’m lost ’cause I found
 The very thought of you, it follows me around

This is a classic case of falling for a friend and not realizing until it hits you in the face one day. You’re confused and disoriented, because you have never looked at that person in this way before.
If I stay in the dark, the light can’t bring me down

What DiRusso means by this is that hiding her feelings feels less painful than confronting the person on what’s going on between them. She would rather ignore the pains of longing, rather than admit these feelings might not be reciprocated.

description.plain:
Infinite Jest is a novel by David Foster Wallace, well known for being popular among
pseudointellectual men.

DiRusso has stated in Instagram posts that, “I wrote this song about being with someone who made me feel small. The process of writing this involved me admitting a lot of things to myself that I had been ignoring. I realized I was with someone who didn’t see or hear me, but simply liked the idea of having someone. It’s also about staying even after I recognized this empty reality, because ultimately – I liked having someone too 💔”
